HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 244
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Jared Allen on being
inducted into the Pro Football Hall of Fame.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing
an outstanding athlete and human being who has attained the very pinnacle of sporting
achievement; and
WHEREAS, Jared Allen, the dominant defensive end who celebrated sacks with his calf-
roping celebration, has been elected to the Pro Football Hall of Fame, Class of 2025; and
WHEREAS, a twelve-year veteran of the National Football League (NFL), Jared Allen
spent the bulk of his career with the Minnesota Vikings (2008-2013); he began his pro football
journey with the Kansas City Chiefs (2004-2007) and later played for the Chicago Bears (2014-
2015) and the Carolina Panthers (2015); and
WHEREAS, he was an instrumental force in the Vikings' 2009 playoff run, which
culminated in the team reaching the NFC Championship Game, and to cap his career, he
helped lead the Carolina Panthers to Super Bowl 50; and
WHEREAS, truly a once-in-a-generation player, Jared Allen started 181 of the 187
regular-season and all seven playoff games he played, earned First-Team All-Pro honors four
times, and was selected to the Pro Bowl five times; and
WHEREAS, Jared Allen's 136 sacks in regular-season games from his rookie season
through his final campaign were the most in the NFL during that span, and this total ranks 12th in
NFL history; and
WHEREAS, his 19 fumble recoveries and 49.5 sacks on third downs were the most
leaguewide from 2004-2015; and
