WHEREAS, Jared Allen is tied for second with two fellow Hall of Famers for most
seasons ranked in the top ten in the NFL in sacks (eight seasons), and his tally of 22 sacks in
2011 is tied for second in NFL history for a season; and
WHEREAS, Jared Allen totaled 641 career tackles (497 solo) and recorded 31 forced
fumbles (19 recoveries), 6 interceptions, and 58 passes defensed; and
WHEREAS, he is the Minnesota franchise leader in safeties and tied for first in NFL
history in that category with 4; he is among the best in tackles for loss in Vikings history (104,
tied for first) and league history (171, tied for 6th among players since 1999); and
WHEREAS, during his tenure in Minnesota, Jared Allen needed just 96 games to tally
85.5 sacks (sixth in franchise history) for an average of 0.89 sacks per game (the highest
average in team history); and
WHEREAS, he has been hailed as a dominant defensive player and sack-master by
such NFL luminaries as Aaron Rodgers, Eli Manning, and Greg Olsen; and
WHEREAS, Jared Allen has already been included in the Vikings Ring of Honor, and he
is greatly honored to enter the Pro Football Hall Fame as a Minnesota Viking; and
WHEREAS, a proud resident of Nashville, Jared Allen is one of the greatest defensive
players in NFL history, and he is most worthy of our approbation on this special occasion; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Jared Allen on being inducted into the Pro
Football Hall of Fame, salute his outstanding NFL career, and extend to him our best wishes for
much continued success and happiness in the future as a Tennessean.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
